<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-09T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="789" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/11–948: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Callanan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-09T17:00:00+08:00">November 9, 1948—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 9—5:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>133. Warning similar to Consulate General Shanghai sent to Americans
                            today—this district north of and bordering on Yangtze.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Callanan</hi></signed></closer>
